    "Considering the subsequent K * → Kπ transition and the kinematics in Fig. 1, the fully differential decay distribution in q 2 and in the angles θ ℓ, θ K *, ϕ has the expressiond 4 Γ( B0 → K * 0 (Kπ)ℓ - 1 ℓ + 2) dq 2 d cos θ ℓ d cos θ K * dϕ = 9 32π I(q 2, θ ℓ, θ K *, ϕ).",
    "(50)The function I(q 2, θ ℓ, θ K *, ϕ) can be written in terms of angular coefficient functionsI (a)i (q 2) using the decomposition [8] I(q 2, θ ℓ, θ K *, ϕ) = I s 1 (q 2) sin 2 θ K * + I c 1 (q 2) cos 2 θ K * + I s 2 (q 2) sin 2 θ K * + I c 2 (q 2) cos 2 θ K * cos 2θ ℓ + I 3 (q 2) sin 2 θ K * sin 2 θ ℓ cos 2ϕ + I 4 (q 2) sin 2θ K * sin 2θ ℓ cos ϕ + I 5 (q 2) sin 2θ K * sin θ ℓ cos ϕ(51)+ I s 6 (q 2) sin 2 θ K * + I c 6 (q 2) cos 2 θ K * cos θ ℓ + I 7 (q 2) sin 2θ K * sin θ ℓ sin ϕ + I 8 (q 2) sin 2θ K * sin 2θ ℓ sin ϕ + I 9 (q 2) sin 2 θ K * sin 2 θ ℓ sin 2ϕ.",
